oc:kn_03a12f6f a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any mock response or test double" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Mock the COMPLETE data structure as it exists in reality, not just the fields your immediate test uses. Partial mocks hide structural assumptions and cause silent downstream failures." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Downstream code may depend on fields you didn't include in the partial mock; tests pass but integration fails, creating false confidence" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_31c2eb0f a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any assertion that references mock elements, test IDs with '-mock', or mock-specific selectors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NEVER test mock behavior — asserting that a mock element exists verifies nothing about real component behavior. Test real components or don't mock them." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tests that verify mock presence pass when the mock is present but prove nothing about actual production behavior, creating false confidence" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_5c6131aa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Gate check before every test assertion, production method addition, or mock creation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before asserting on a mock: ask 'Am I testing real behavior or mock existence?' If mock existence → stop, delete assertion or unmock component. Before adding a production method: ask 'Is this only used by tests?' If yes → put in test utilities. Before mocking: ask 'What side effects does the real method have? Does this test depend on them?' If depends → mock at lower level." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These gate functions catch anti-patterns at the moment of creation rather than during review" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_914ad6be a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before adding any method to a production class" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NEVER add test-only methods to production classes. If a method is only called in test files, it belongs in test utilities, not production code." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Test-only methods pollute production APIs, violate YAGNI, risk accidental production calls, and confuse object lifecycle with entity lifecycle" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a987a19a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When mock complexity exceeds test complexity" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If mock setup is longer than test logic, or you're mocking everything to make a test pass, consider using integration tests with real components instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-complex mocks indicate the test is fighting the architecture; integration tests with real components are often simpler and more trustworthy" .

oc:kn_cb2094df a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always — these are non-negotiable rules for all testing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The three Iron Laws: (1) NEVER test mock behavior, (2) NEVER add test-only methods to production classes, (3) NEVER mock without understanding dependencies." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Violating any of these laws produces tests that give false confidence and hide real defects" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_d50c0113 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any test or implementation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Following strict TDD prevents all these anti-patterns: write test first, watch it fail, implement minimally, then refactor. If you're testing mock behavior, you violated TDD." ;
    oc:hasRationale "TDD forces you to think about what you're testing before adding mocks, ensures tests verify real behavior, and prevents test-only code from creeping into production" .

oc:kn_ed0d1031 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before mocking any method or dependency" ;
    oc:directiveContent "NEVER mock a dependency without understanding its side effects. The real method may have side effects your test depends on, and mocking it will silently break test logic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Blind mocking can suppress side effects the test relies on, causing tests to pass for wrong reasons or fail mysteriously" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

